'''Dawid Boois''' (born 13 January 1952) is a [[Namibia]]n politician and educator. A member of [[SWAPO]], Boois was the Governor of the southern [[ǁKaras Region]] and a member of the [[National Assembly of Namibia|National Assembly]] from 2000-2005.<ref name=NID>[http://www.nid.org.na/view_book_entry.php?book_id=25 Dawid Boois] Namibia Institute for Democracy</ref> In the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2010|2010 regional elections]], Boois won the [[Berseba Constituency]] with 1,225 votes.<ref>[http://www.ecn.na/results/2010/Press_Release_Constituency_Berseba.pdf Election results from Electoral Commission of Namibia] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717175924/http://www.ecn.na/results/2010/Press_Release_Constituency_Berseba.pdf |date=2011-07-17 }}</ref> He remained Berseba councillor also after the [[Namibian local and regional elections, 2015|2015 regional elections]] which he won with 1,774 votes.<ref>{{Cite web | title= Regional Council Election Results 2015 | publisher = [[Electoral Commission of Namibia]] | date=3 December 2015 | page=1 | url=http://www.ecn.na/documents/27857/223442/Regional+Counils+Election+Results_Duly+elected+candidates+2015.pdf/32493774-80b3-4be3-9ca1-1f6ce187673a?version=1.0}}</ref> As an educator, Boois was a teacher at the Ecumenical Community Secondary School in [[Berseba]].<ref name=NID/>
Boois was involved in a controversy regarding the different factions of the [[traditional leader]]ship of the ǀHaiǀKhaua ([[Berseba Orlam]]) subtribe of the [[Nama people]]. He supported a group contesting the legitimacy of the reunification of the Goliath and Isaak rival clans and tried to extend the 50-year-long split of the Berseba [[Orlam]]. Eventually Boois supported the unity of the tribe by reconciling with fellow former Karas governor [[Stephanus Goliath]] early in 2011.<ref>[http://www.namibian.com.na/news/full-story/archive/2011/february/article/boois-and-goliath-bury-the-hatchet/ Boois and Goliath bury the hatchet] ''[[The Namibian]]'', 25 February 2011</ref>
==Business interests== According to transparency documents released in 2003 while Boois was a member of the National Assembly, the Berseba-native is a director of Kaiseb Fishing. He also owns 8% of the shares in the company. He also owns over 15,000 shares in Southern Namibia Hake Fishing Industries alongside fellow SWAPO politician [[Willem Konjore]]. He also owns a restaurant and hotel in ǁKaras Region.<ref name=NID/>
