{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Jonuz Kaceli | image = | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = Jonuz Kaceli | birth_name = Jonuz Osman Kaceli | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1908|06|20}} <!-- {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = [[Tirana]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1951|02|25|1908|06|20}} <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth) --> | death_place = [[Tirana]] | body_discovered = 1992 | death_cause = execution | resting_place = [[Tirana]] | resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|display=inline,title}} --> | monuments = | residence = | nationality = [[Albanians|Albanian]] | citizenship = [[Albanians|Albanian]] | other_names = | known_for = Benefactory deeds | television = | education = | alma_mater = | employer = | organization = [[Osman Kaceli e djemtë]] | notable works = | style = | influences = | influenced = | agent = | occupation = Businessman | years_active = 1930 - 1951 | home_town = | salary = | networth = | height = | weight = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | movement = | opponents = | boards = | criminal_charge = [[Massacre of 1951 in Albania|No proces]] | criminal_penalty = [[Massacre of 1951 in Albania|Dead penalty]] | criminal_status = [[Innocent]] after proces of 1991 <ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=kygUAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA3-PA2 report: East Europe, Nummers 152-161], Google Books</ref> | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relations = | callsign = | awards = [[Civil awards and decorations of Albania|Martyr of Democracy]] | signature = | signature_alt = | website = | footnotes = | box_width = | misc = }}
'''Jonuz Kaceli''' (20 Juni 1908– 25 February 1951) was an [[Albanians|Albanian]] businessman and dissident of the [[Communist Albania|communist regime]] in Albania. He was one of the 23 victims of the regime's [[Massacre of 1951 in Albania]].<ref>http://www.zemrashqiptare.net/article/Historia/7046/</ref>
==Life== Jonuz Kaceli was born in 1908 in [[Tirana]]. Prior to his arrest and killing, he had been a well known businessman in [[Albania]], as the co-owner in the company [[Osman Kaceli e djemtë]], which had been one of the first companies registered in [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] after the [[Albanian Declaration of Independence]] in 1912. He was also the brother of [[Sadik Kaceli]], a famous Albanian painter. [[Qemal Stafa]], a notable World War II hero, had been a company employee prior to his death in 1942.<ref>Libri: Bombe ne ambassades Sovjetik</ref>
==Importance== Kaceli had been an important person in the business community of Tirana.<ref name="Telegraf">Telegraf published on 9 march 2008 [http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kaceli_Article_1.jpg]{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} and [http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Kaceli_article_part_4.jpg]{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He allegedly tried to hurt [[Mehmet Shehu]] during such interrogations. As a result, according to a witness who told the story in 1993, he was thrown from the second floor of the Ministry of the Interior building and thus killed one day prior to the rest of the victims of the massacre, on 25 February 1951.<ref>Uran Butka 27 February 2006 Shekulli newspaper</ref><ref>[http://www.zemrashqiptare.net/article/Historia/7742/?highlight=jonuz+kaceli&match= Aleksandër Meksi: Edhe njëherë mbi bombën në Ambasadën sovjetike], ZemraShqiptare.net, 12-04-2009, 07:16pm (GMT)</ref> He was survived by wife and seven children, all of whom were sent to Albanian [[gulags]] after the killing took place.<ref name="Telegraf"/>
==Recognition== In 2008 his act was recognized by the President of Albania, [[Bamir Topi]] and Kaceli was duly awarded post mortem the medal of [[Civil awards and decorations of Albania|Martyr of Democracy]]. His corpse is now buried at the Albanian [[National Martyrs Cemetery of Albania|National Martyrs Cemetery]] ({{lang-sq|Dëshmorët e Kombit}}).<ref>[http://www.president.al/shqip/info.asp?id=4905 Decorations in 2008 from the President of Albania]</ref>
==See also== *[[List of the victims of the Albanian communist regime]] *[[Sadik Kaceli]]
